_title    = [[Be Without You]]\n| prev_year     = 2005\n| next_title    = [[Enough Cryin]]\n| next_year     = 2006\n| misc = \n{{Extra chronology\n | artist     = U2\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = Sgt. Pepper's Lonely Hearts Club Band\n | prev_year  = 2005\n | title      = One\n | year       = 2006\n | next_title = [[The Saints Are Coming#U2 and Green Day cover|The Saints Are Coming]]\n | next_year  = 2006\n}}\n{{External music video|{{Youtube|ZpDQJnI4OhU|\"One\"}}}}\n}}\n \n'''\"One\"''' is the second international single from [[Mary J. Blige]]'s seventh studio album, ''[[The Breakthrough]]'', featuring U2. After being invited to join the group on stage at their New York gig in 2005, Blige performed the track with U2 and received a standing ovation.{{Citation needed|date=February 2018}} The song was then recorded featuring Blige on lead vocals, with Bono supplying additional vocals and the band performing the music. It was released on 3 April 2006, having already been featured heavily on [[BBC Radio 1]]'s playlist, and has been a staple record on Capital FM's playlist since late January. The song was a major commercial success in Europe, reaching number two in Ireland and the United Kingdom and topping the [[VG-lista|Norwegian Singles Chart]] for six weeks. The cover also reached number one in Austria for a week and reached the top 10 in several other European countries.\n\n===Live performances===\nIn May 2006, Blige performed the song at the finale of ''[[American Idol]]'' with finalist [[Elliott Yamin]], ahead of its full release to American radio.<ref>https://www.cbsnews.com/pictures/american-idol-ends-with-a-bang/4/</ref> It was also used by [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] for its end-of-season montage after game five of the [[2006 World Series]].<ref>http://www.cbs.com/shows/grammys/photos/1005729/we-can-t-stop-rewatching-these-legendary-grammy-performances/102485/mary-j-blige-and-u2-2006-/</ref>\n\n===Track listing===\n'''CD single'''\n{{Track listing\n| headline  = CD 01<ref>https://www.discogs.com/Mary-J-Blige-And-U2-One/release/1583476</ref>\n| title1  = One\n| length1 = 4:04\n| lyrics1 = Bono\n| extra1  =\n| note1   = radio edit\n| title2  = Can't Hide From Luv\n| length2 = 3:52\n| lyrics2 = \n| extra2 =\n| note2   = live\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline  = CD 02<ref>https://www.discogs.com/Mary-J-Blige-And-U2-One/release/1583464</ref>\n| title1  = One\n| length1 = 4:04\n| lyrics1 = Bono\n| extra1  =\n| note1   = radio edit\n| title2  = I'm Goin' Down\n| length2 = 3:24\n| lyrics2 = \n| extra2   =\n| note2   = Live at the Cipriani Wall Street Concert Series\n| title3 = My Life '05\n| length3 = 3:24\n| lyrics3 = \n| extra3 =\n}}\n\n===Credits===\n*Written by [[Bono]], [[Adam Clayton]], [[The Edge]], [[Larry Mullen Jr]]\n*Produced by Ron Fair\n*Co-producered by Tal Herzberg\n*Lead vocals performed by Mary J Blige\n*Additional vocals and rhythm guitar performed by Bono\n*Lead guitar performed by The Edge\n*Bass performed by Adam Clayton\n*Drums and percussion performed by Larry Mullen Jr\n*Strings arranged and conducted by Ron Fair\n*Piano and organ performed by Ron Fair\n*Additional electric and acoustic guitar performed by John Goux\n*Mixed by Jack Joseph\n*Executive producer: Mary J. Blige\n\n===Charts and certifications===\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n====Weekly charts====\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (2006)\n!Peak<br>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|1|artist=Mary J Blige and U2|song=One|accessdate=15 February 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders|6|artist=Mary J Blige and U2|song=One|accessdate=15 February 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia|10|artist=Mary J Blige and U2|song=One|accessdate=15 February 2018}}\n|-\n|{{single chart|Czech Republic|28|year=2006|week=36|rowheader=true|accessdate=12 September 2018}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Danish|7|artist=Mary J Blige and U2|song=One|accessdate=15 February 2018}}\n|-\n|Europe ([[European Hot 100 Singles]]){{citation needed|date=February 2018}}\n|align=\