==Year-end charts====\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Chart (2006)\n!Position\n|-\n|Austria (\u00d63 Austria Top 40)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://austriancharts.at/year.asp?cat=s&id=2006|title=Jahreshitparade Singles 2006|language=German|accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|10\n|-\n|Belgium (Ultratop 50 Flanders)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ultratop.be/nl/annual.asp?year=2006|title=Jaaroverzichten 2006|publisher=[[Ultratop]]|language=Dutch|accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|16\n|-\n|Belgium (Ultratop 50 Wallonia)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ultratop.be/fr/annual.asp?year=2006|title=Rapports annuels 2006|publisher=[[Ultratop]]|language=French|accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|35\n|-\n|Germany (Official German Charts)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.offiziellecharts.de/charts/single-jahr/for-date-2006|title=Top 100 Singles - Jahrescharts 2006|publisher=[[GfK Entertainment]]|language=German|accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|24\n|-\n|Ireland (IRMA)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.irma.ie/#verticalTab11|title=Best of singles 2006|publisher=[[Irish Recorded Music Association|IRMA]]|accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|15\n|-\n|Netherlands (Dutch Top 40)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.top40.nl/bijzondere-lijsten/top-100-jaaroverzichten/2006|title=Top 100-Jaaroverzicht van 2006|publisher=Dutch Top 40|accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|6\n|-\n|Netherlands (Single Top 100)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dutchcharts.nl/jaaroverzichten.asp?year=2006&cat=s|title=Jaaroverzichten 2006|publisher=[[MegaCharts]]|language=Dutch|accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|11\n|-\n|Switzerland (Schweizer Hitparade)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.swisscharts.com/charts/jahreshitparade/2006|title=Swiss Year-End Charts 2006|language=German|accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|11\n|-\n|UK Singles (Official Charts Company)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/end-of-year-singles-chart/20060108/37501/|title=End of Year Singles Chart Top 100 - 2006|publisher=[[The Official Charts Company]]|accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|35\n|}\n\n====Certifications====\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Germany|artist=Mary J. Blige feat U2|title=One|award=Gold|type=single|relyear=2006|certyear=2018|accessdate=May 1, 2018}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Italy|artist=Mary J. Blige & U2|title=One|award=Gold|type=single|relyear=2006|digital=true|accessdate=December 1, 2017}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|artist=Mary J. Blige & U2|title=One|award=Silver|type=single|relyear=2006|digital=true|accessdate=1 December 2017}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Other covers==\n\"One\" has been covered by numerous other artists, including [[Damien Rice]], [[Johnny Logan (singer)|Johnny Logan]], [[Johnny Cash]], [[Adam Lambert]], [[Howie Day]], [[Joe Cocker]], [[Warren Haynes]], [[R.E.M.]], [[Gregorian (band)|Gregorian]], [[Pearl Jam]], [[Kendall Payne]], [[Shinedown]], [[Vanessa Paradis]] & [[Alain Lanty]], [[Cowboy Junkies]] and the cast of the television series ''[[Glee (TV series)|Glee]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.upvenue.com/article/1171-u2-one-covers.html|title=U2 One Covers|publisher=}}</ref>\n\nUnder a [[Supergroup (music)|supergroup]] label of \"Automatic Baby\" (reflecting the names of then recent releases by both groups), members of R.E.M. and U2 played an acoustic version of the song during a 1993 MTV concert for then newly-inaugurated U.S. president [[Bill Clinton]].<ref>{{cite magazine| url = https://www.rollingstone.com/music/videos/see-u2-rem-play-bill-clinton-inauguration-as-automatic-baby-w461445 | magazine = Rolling Stone | title = Flashback: U2 and REM Join Forces for Bill Clinton Inauguration | accessdate= 23 February 2017 }}</ref> In 1997 this version of \"One\" reached number one in Iceland and ended the year as the country's 12th-most-successful single.<ref>{{cite newspaper|url=https://timarit.is/page/2950035?iabr=on#page/n1/mode/2up/|title=\u00cdslenski Listinn Topp 40 (16.1. '97 \u201322.1. '97)|newspaper=[[DV (newspaper)|Dagbla\u00f0i\u00f0 V\u00edsir]]|language=is|page=16|date=17 January 1997|access-date=21 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite newspaper|url=https://timarit.is/page/2963913?iabr=on#page/n15/mode/2up/|title=\u00c1rslistinn 1997 \u2013 \u00cdslenski Listinn \u2013 100 Vins\u00e6lustu L\u00f6gin|newspaper=[[DV (newspaper)|Dagbla\u00f0i\u00f0 V\u00edsir]]|language=is|page=25|date=2 January 1998|access-date=21 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Damien Rice]] reworked the song for the 2011 tribute album ''[[AHK-toong BAY-bi Covered]]''. \"I remember seeing the queues on Dublin's [[Grafton Street]]: people waiting, sleeping, for the first copies of the new U2 record, as if some famine had hit the soul of the music world,\" he remarked. \"Two decades later, I busked for the homeless with Bono on the same street. We played 'One' and Bono appeared to forget the words, but I didn't \u2013 they were as clear to me as the [[Lord's Prayer|Our Father]]. Seventeen ''(Rice's age when Achtung Baby was issued)'' is such a powerful age, and 'One' is such a powerful song.\"<ref>\"What's On Your Free CD?\", ''[[Q (magazine)|Q]]'', December 2011, pp6\u20137</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of covers of U2 songs#One|List of covers of U2 songs \u2013 One]]\n* [[List of number-one singles of 1992 (Ireland)]]\n* [[List of RPM number-one singles of 1992]]\n* [[List of number-one mainstream rock hits (United States)#1992|List of number-one mainstream rock hits (United States)]]\n* [[List of number-one hits of 2006 (Austria)]]\n* [[List of number-one songs in Norway]]\n* [[Number one modern rock hits of 1992]]\n\n== References ==\n\n=== Footnotes ===\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n=== Bibliography ===\n{{refbegin}}\n* {{Citation |title=U2: An Irish Phenomenon|first=Vi\u0161nja|last=Cogan|year=2008|publi